All Classes

Class Description
ArrayVector
The ArrayVector class is an implementations of the Vector interface, that represent a vector in the system.
InvalidParameterProvided
The exception is thrown when an invalid parameter is passed as an argument.
InvalidVectorDimension
The exception is thrown when the program wants to create a vector with invalid dimensions, or when two or more vectors are interacting with each other and they are in different dimensions.
NullArgumentProvided
The exception is thrown when the program is processing on a null argument passed where the system doesn't expect a null argument.
Vector
The Vector interface.
VectorOperations
The class provides a way to manipulate 2 or more vectors.
